Text: Progress Report EWS Coordinationis a progress report on the agenda items that were prepared in our last meeting We can discuss completion items during our meeting tomorrow Jim

Final Changes to existing Large Commodity Formis the final redline showing all the changes made to our existing large commodity form based on the spot check item in the EESEWS Coordination Plan We will drive these changes into all remaining forms midmarket CMA FastTrack and industrial and commercial gas agreements as well as all transactions currently in the beginning or middle stages of negotiation On a go forward basis for new transactions we will identify and explain all material deviations from these revised forms Jim

Re Supply Deals They are Back Cc If that is the decision please let Shelly know that I would like to discuss the matter Let Cathy know and she can schedule a meeting If Jeff Hodge should attend please arrange that also Jim Christina Finelli PM To James E ES Paul ES Mike D ES Sarah ES Edwin ES Kelly ES cc Subject Supply Deals They are Back Just to let you know I am meeting with Shelly Stubbs at PM today I assume she will officially advise me of Don Blacks decision to continue trading under EES and that we will continue to paper their deals Jim if you want to attend that would be great Let me know Christy

Re Q Dealswe can discuss at our call Jim Enron Energy Services From Vicki Sharp AM Phone No To James E ES cc Subject Q Deals Please discuss a plan with Jeff Hodge for how to promptly get review of these contracts and report back to me Forwarded by Vicki SharpHOUEES on AM Janet R Dietrich PM To Michael ES Jeremy ES Angela ES Craig H ES Greg ES Scott ES James M ES Richard L ES Sean A ES Don ES Rogers ct James W ES Gayle W ES Vicki ES Ozzie ES cc Subject Q Deals Just to ensure were all on the same page here following are the priority deals for Q We really need to be sure we are all closely coordinated and very focused on bringing these to closure Mann Harrahs Sysco Danacorp Muench Tyco Quebecor Schwarz Park Place Entertainment Sutter Consolidated Container Corp Sharp Various commodity deals We cant afford internal downtime on these deals and we need everyone to step up to make them happen Let me know if I can help

Re FW Electric Energy Sales Services AgreementDOC Cc is one of the deals on the list we discussed this morning Since it is on the fastest track we need to discuss at our meeting tomorrow Cathy will coordinate with you to set up a time Jim Deborah Asmus PM To James E ES cc Subject FW Electric Energy Sales Services AgreementDOC Forwarded by Deborah AsmusHOUEES on PM Katz Aaron katz ORPSyscocom on PM To cc Taylor Terry Taylor ORPSYSCOcom Berke Kent berke ORPSyscocom Subject FW Electric Energy Sales Services AgreementDOC Debbie Attached is a draft of the referenced agreement which has been redlined to reflect Syscos comments The draft has not been reviewed completely by me or at all by Syscos business people so it remains subject to additional comments I will see you at pm Aaron Electric Energy Sales Services AgreementDOC

Pending Dealsadd a transaction with ANCRexam to our pending list for your review This is one that we are in negotiations with the customer and should close by the end of the month Ths restructure will fix a substantial outstanding receivable in addition to creating new origination Jim
Deal overviews Cc to schedule time to present overview presentations for the following deals Harrahs DanaCorp Quebecor Consolidated Container Please let me know your availability this coming week Jim

Sutter Health Cc for your review and comments Jim Forwarded by James E KellerHOUEES on AM Enron Energy Services From Andrew Wu PM Phone No To Dennis ES George ES Lamar ES cc James E ES Mike D ES Robert C nronXGate Subject Sutter Health Attached to this email pls find my revised Sutter document incorporating our thoughts and comments to date Pls advise with comments or questions Jim Keller will you be the one taking care of coordinating legal review with ENA or is it someone else Thanks AW

PacTel Revised Commodity Agmtme know your availability to discuss Jim Forwarded by James E KellerHOUEES on AM Enron Energy Services From Andrew Wu PM Phone No To Dennis ES Dan ES Eric ES Marty ES Evan ES Don ES Denise nronXGate Beth ES Mike D ES James E ES Robert C nronXGate Vicki ES Elizabeth CT cc Subject PacTel Revised Commodity Agmt Attached to this email pls find the latest version of the subject agreement incorporating the thoughts and comments received to date including PacTels comments Note that there are number of outstanding issues We will be working off this version commencing Monday pm May in SBCs offices in San Ramon I have also included a redline against the version that we sent to PacTel Pls email comments questions etc and Ill be able to pick them up from the Enron San Ramon office If you need to get a hold of me in person the best way is to send me an email page to AW
